@node intro "Introduction"

@{b}@{u} What is it for?@{ub}@{uu}

	This  program  just  ensures  that user's alias does not
	contain  any  illegal  characters,  like  spaces.  If it
	detects  spaces  in  the  Alias,  it  will ask for a new
	Alias.

	Optionally  it will also check that every user (who runs
	this  program)  will  have a different Alias!  For this,
	CheckAlias needs the database Generated by @{"FixAlias" link fixalias}

	It's  very  useful  for  DLG systems which have Internet
	e-mail  and  Usenet  News available for users.  Internet
	address  may  not contain (to my knowledge) no spaces in
	it.   If  you have forced ALIASES to be used as USERNAME
	in the internet-address then this utility is for you.

@endnode

@node require "Requirements"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

	 OS2.04 required and a working @{"Dialog Pro BBS" link dialog} sofware!

	 It was compiled with SAS/C V6.51 and should work nicely
	without Gurus or Crashes.

@endnode

@node dialog "What is DLG?"

 @{b}@{u}Hmm, DLG? What does it mean?@{ub}@{uu}

	 DLG stands for Dialog Professional BB/OS.  It's really amazing
	package  from  Telepro  Technologies.  There's so many features
	within this software so I won't start listing them here.

	 If  you  like  to  know more about DLG.  Call ANY BBS which is
	running with it.  I think you will see what I mean.

@endnode

@node install "Installing CheckAlias"

 @{b}@{u}Great, But How do I install it?@{ub}@{uu}

	Here's STEP-BY-STEP instructions:

	1) Take a deep breath!

	2) Consider twice do you need this program!

	3) Make a barrel of coffee, and drink it!

	4) Copy the executable "CheckAlias" somewhere.

	   eg.	Copy CheckAlias DLGOWN:

	   (I use secondary assign and directory for third party
	    DLG utilities)

	5)  Put  it in the script where you need it, for example the
	    starting script of TIN or ELM etc..

		Check for @{"OPERATIONAL PARAMETERS" link paramet}

@endnode

@node paramet "Calling Parameters & Operation"

 @{b}@{u}Parameters passed to CheckAlias in Commandline@{ub}@{uu}

	Call String. Parameters can be in any order!

	CheckAlias [QUIET] [-l<length>] [-v] [-s]

	@{u}QUIET@{uu}	If  this parameter is specified, CheckAlias will
		operate as quietly as possible.  Ie.  no queries
		etc.

		If  QUIET  is  not specified, user can enter the
		alias  she/he  wants to use.  QUIET is overrided
		if users Alias is a DUPLICATE!

	@{u}-l<l>@{uu}	if  specified,  CheckAlias will limit the length
		of  the  alias  to  8 characters in default.  If
		length  specified  after -l then CheckAlias will
		use that instead of 8.
		Possible lengts are from 8 to 35

	@{u}-s@{uu}	Suggest alias, based on username.
		example. Username is 'Erno Tuomainen'
		suggestion would be  'ETuomainen'

		Truncated to the length you specify with -l

	@{u}-v@{uu}	Suppress all credits! And program version info!

	This  program  must be run ON-LINE!  Either from menu or
	some  script.   It  takes  all the needed stuff directly
	from DLG with couple of dlg.library calls.

		@{"Hit here for examples" link examples}

@{u}Important NOTE!@{uu}

	If  you  are using Wim Rumpings @{"FixAlias" link fixalias} CheckAlias will
	utilize  that  too!   CheckAlias  will  use the database
	generated by FIXALIAS!  But you must run FixAlias DAILY,
	make an cronevent entry for FixAlias.

	With  this  database  this program assures that no ALIAS
	can   be   used  multiple  times!   Every  user  running
	CheckAlias program will have different alias.

	CheckAlias will also update this database for any changes!

@endnode

@node examples "Some examples"

 @{b}@{u}Examples@{ub}@{uu}

@{u}CheckAlias@{uu}

	Normal  operation.   No  length  limiting,  show version
	info,  do  not  suggest alias and ask user to type a new
	alias if the old alias is invalid.

@{u}CheckAlias -l@{uu}

	Same as above but alias will be limited to 8 characters.

@{u}CheckAlias -l10 -v -s@{uu}

	Suppress version info.
	IF  user's  alias is illegal (too long, contains spaces)
	CheckAlias  will  ask for a replacement, alias length is
	limited  to  10  characters and a suggestion is made for
	alias.

@{u}CheckAlias -l10 -v -s quiet@{uu}

	Same  as above, but all will be done silently.  If alias
	is  incorrect  it  will  be replaced with the suggestion
	CheckAlias  mades,  automatically and it will be limited
	to 10 characters.  IF suggested alias is already used by
	some  other  user  CheckAlias  will ask user to type the
	alias!

@endnode

@node fixalias "Wim Rumping's FixAlias"

 @{b}@{u}FixAlias, what it is?@{ub}@{uu}

	 FixAlias will generate a database collecting each users
	name  and  alias  into it.  This database is very useful
	because  DLG  does  not  keep record of Aliases, and DLG
	also  allows  multiple aliases.  CheckAlias will utilize
	FixAlias's databases to ensure that no duplicate Aliases
	are used.

	 This database is stored at  DlgConfig:MISC/Alias.Idx

 It's format is like this:

	struct UserAlias_Entry
	  {
	    char Alias[36];
	    char Name[36];
	  };

	@{u}@{b}CheckAlias will UPDATE this database!@{uu}@{ub}

@endnode

@node distrib "Distribution"

 @{b}@{u}Distribution & Copyrights@{ub}@{uu}

	 This  program  is  Copyright by Author (Erno Tuomainen) but is
	released as a CARDWARE product.  You can spread this as long as
	all  the  files  (unmodified!)  are  included  in  this archive
	(CHKALIAS.LHA) and no money is involved in the process.

	 You  can always use "Version CheckAlias" to specify the
	current version of the executable!

	 I  didn't  include  sources  for  this  door  in this Release.
	Source  is  a  LITTLE  messy  at  the moment and there are some
	things  I  would  like  to  include  in the final version so be
	patient.   I  will  release  a  new  version with C-source code
	within the archive.

	 If  you  are continually using this program, please send me an
	NICE postcard so I know who's using it.  And Postcards are nice
	and doesn't cost much!  :)
@endnode

